ractive proof. This result extends the result of Goldreich, Micali and Wigderson, that, under the same assumption, all of NP admits zero-knowledge interactive proofs. Assuming envelopes for bit commitment, we show that every language that admits an interactive proof admits a perfect zero-knowledge interactive proof.</abstract></paper>